WEBVTT

00:00:03.107 --> 00:00:08.113
DEPARTMENT OF DIETETICS INTERVIEW VENUE

00:00:08.196 --> 00:00:09.572
Please have a seat.

00:00:10.115 --> 00:00:10.949
Thank you.

00:00:12.033 --> 00:00:16.162
Mr. Hase, I see that you have been
working at a restaurant for three years.

00:00:17.038 --> 00:00:21.793
What have you learned, or how did you grow
as a person during your time there?

00:00:26.506 --> 00:00:28.591
Working in the restaurant business

00:00:29.175 --> 00:00:31.678
has made me realize how much joy

00:00:32.804 --> 00:00:35.306
comes from feeding people,
and how much of an impact

00:00:36.057 --> 00:00:38.393
food has on the mind and body.

00:00:39.144 --> 00:00:41.396
Out of all the onigiri I've had in Japan,

00:00:41.479 --> 00:00:42.772
this is the best.

00:00:42.856 --> 00:00:43.898
It's good.

00:00:44.816 --> 00:00:46.943
Your cooking is the best!

00:00:47.026 --> 00:00:48.319
It was so delicious!

00:00:48.403 --> 00:00:51.281
It has a very deep flavor.

00:00:52.365 --> 00:00:53.533
From now on,

00:00:55.160 --> 00:00:58.538
I want to use all of my experiences
to my advantage,

00:00:59.914 --> 00:01:02.125
whether I fail or succeed,

00:01:03.001 --> 00:01:06.045
and support all athletes in any situation

00:01:06.129 --> 00:01:07.839
through the meals that I make.

00:01:10.884 --> 00:01:13.344
That's the kind of person
I wish to become.

00:01:14.220 --> 00:01:18.391
TANOMI

00:01:20.935 --> 00:01:22.520
-Hello.
-Hello.

00:01:24.022 --> 00:01:25.231
How was your interview?

00:01:27.108 --> 00:01:30.528
I was able
to say everything that I prepared.

00:01:31.112 --> 00:01:31.946
That's good.

00:01:37.535 --> 00:01:39.078
This place lets you enroll

00:01:39.162 --> 00:01:42.707
in a special class for sports dietetics
from your second year.

00:01:43.374 --> 00:01:46.878
And their scholarship program
is a lot more generous than I expected.

00:01:47.503 --> 00:01:48.671
There's even an overseas training program.

00:01:48.755 --> 00:01:49.923
Really?

00:01:50.006 --> 00:01:51.966
Wow…

00:01:55.887 --> 00:02:00.516
CLOSED

00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:04.896
TANOMI

00:02:06.481 --> 00:02:11.778
OPEN

00:03:24.726 --> 00:03:27.395
You're still sleeping?

00:03:27.478 --> 00:03:28.396
Here.

00:03:28.479 --> 00:03:30.148
I bought you breakfast.

00:03:31.607 --> 00:03:34.152
Just ten more minutes…

00:03:34.694 --> 00:03:39.073
Hey, aren't you going
to your intern job today?

00:03:49.667 --> 00:03:52.670
So it all depends on your presentation
for the contest, huh?

00:03:52.754 --> 00:03:53.588
Yeah.

00:03:55.298 --> 00:03:58.259
Wow, you're amazing, Rin.

00:03:58.343 --> 00:04:00.219
You're doing
your graduation project too, right?

00:04:00.928 --> 00:04:02.305
But I'm having fun.

00:04:03.264 --> 00:04:06.768
I've always thought that
creating art was something you do alone.

00:04:06.851 --> 00:04:09.312
But at work, everyone shares their ideas

00:04:09.395 --> 00:04:12.982
and shares the work
and operates as a team. So it's really…

00:04:16.778 --> 00:04:18.279
What's the word again?

00:04:19.572 --> 00:04:22.325
Oh, right! I feel a sense of fulfillment.

00:04:40.593 --> 00:04:42.261
ORGANIC INGREDIENTS
DERIVED FROM DANDELIONS

00:05:11.374 --> 00:05:12.208
So cute!

00:05:12.291 --> 00:05:14.252
-It's getting better and better.
-Yeah.

00:05:14.335 --> 00:05:16.712
-It's so cute.
-I really like it.

00:05:16.796 --> 00:05:18.256
The necktie is great!

00:05:18.339 --> 00:05:19.382
Yeah.

00:05:20.883 --> 00:05:22.844
It just needs a little something more…

00:05:23.553 --> 00:05:25.138
For example…

00:05:25.221 --> 00:05:26.389
Ms. Park,

00:05:26.472 --> 00:05:29.183
how about adding an accent color here?

00:05:29.267 --> 00:05:30.768
Maybe something like silver?

00:05:31.769 --> 00:05:32.728
I see.

00:05:33.354 --> 00:05:35.523
Thank you. I'll try that.

00:05:36.399 --> 00:05:37.775
It will make it even better.

00:05:57.211 --> 00:05:58.629
A DANDELION FAIRY THAT SOLVES SKIN ISSUES

00:05:58.713 --> 00:06:01.048
"Kindness, gently blooming on your skin."

00:06:01.132 --> 00:06:04.135
We took your catchphrase
and combined it with…

00:06:07.138 --> 00:06:09.182
‎A CHICK THAT WAS BORN FROM A DANDELION
‎POPOPIYO

00:06:11.309 --> 00:06:16.063
the color and shape of a dandelion,
which is a main ingredient,

00:06:16.147 --> 00:06:17.607
to come up with Popopiyo.

00:06:19.567 --> 00:06:23.070
Popopiyo is a chick
that was born from a dandelion.

00:06:23.154 --> 00:06:27.325
Despite his cute appearance,
he is actually mischievous

00:06:27.408 --> 00:06:31.662
and bold and loves to travel
around the world.

00:06:32.663 --> 00:06:37.418
And he also helps people
with their skin issues.

00:06:37.501 --> 00:06:38.336
‎MERCHANDISING EXAMPLES

00:06:38.419 --> 00:06:42.882
Popopiyo is
a likeable and heartwarming character.

00:06:42.965 --> 00:06:45.134
I am certain that it will appeal

00:06:45.218 --> 00:06:47.595
to the people in Japan
in their teens and twenties,

00:06:47.678 --> 00:06:49.931
which is our target demographic.

00:06:52.975 --> 00:06:55.770
That is all for my presentation.

00:06:55.853 --> 00:06:57.021
‎THANK YOU VERY MUCH!

00:06:57.104 --> 00:06:58.940
Thank you very much.

00:06:59.023 --> 00:07:00.816
Okay, thank you.

00:07:09.992 --> 00:07:11.536
That's an interesting idea.

00:07:11.619 --> 00:07:14.789
Thank you for working on that
in such a short time.

00:07:21.420 --> 00:07:22.797
Gamsahamnida.

00:07:31.305 --> 00:07:33.558
Thank you very much.

00:07:33.641 --> 00:07:35.560
All right, well then…

00:07:35.643 --> 00:07:36.852
That's awesome!

00:07:37.562 --> 00:07:39.647
It's so cute!

00:07:39.730 --> 00:07:41.482
I'm sure you'll get a good response!

00:07:41.566 --> 00:07:42.817
Thank you.

00:07:43.651 --> 00:07:44.694
Wow…

00:07:46.070 --> 00:07:47.697
That reminds me…

00:07:47.780 --> 00:07:50.157
Your enrollment results
come in soon, right?

00:07:50.241 --> 00:07:51.492
Yeah.

00:07:51.576 --> 00:07:55.371
But the number of openings
for working adults is limited,

00:07:55.454 --> 00:07:58.416
so to be honest, I might not get accepted.

00:08:00.167 --> 00:08:01.752
I'm pretty worried about that.

00:08:04.422 --> 00:08:07.466
And plus, as I was studying,
I realized that

00:08:08.092 --> 00:08:12.305
there is so much more to learn about food
than I had imagined.

00:08:14.015 --> 00:08:17.518
It feels like I'm starting my training
all over again.

00:08:19.729 --> 00:08:23.524
It seems like both of us
are always in training.

00:08:24.108 --> 00:08:25.359
That's true.

00:08:26.527 --> 00:08:29.614
But I feel like I can gain

00:08:30.114 --> 00:08:33.993
a different perspective,
once I get past this.

00:08:34.076 --> 00:08:38.247
I understand that feeling.
It's exciting to have a wall to climb.

00:08:38.331 --> 00:08:39.957
It means we can level up.

00:08:41.042 --> 00:08:43.544
I have to work hard
on my graduation project

00:08:43.628 --> 00:08:45.046
and job hunt too.

00:08:47.757 --> 00:08:48.591
Hey, Rin…

00:08:52.470 --> 00:08:54.930
I know you're looking
for a job in Japan but…

00:08:57.600 --> 00:08:59.185
Does your mother know about this?

00:09:05.483 --> 00:09:08.903
What happened to that instructor position?

00:09:11.572 --> 00:09:16.077
I do have to respond to her
about that soon but…

00:09:16.702 --> 00:09:17.995
I kind of…

00:09:19.246 --> 00:09:21.123
don't have the courage.

00:09:23.376 --> 00:09:27.713
Is that because she might be against it?

00:09:40.893 --> 00:09:44.021
Since this is the path you chose
after so much contemplation,

00:09:44.814 --> 00:09:46.816
if you are honest and tell her,

00:09:47.775 --> 00:09:51.153
I'm sure your mother will understand.

00:09:52.947 --> 00:09:54.115
It will be all right.

00:10:03.332 --> 00:10:07.044
Once I get the results for the contest,
I'll contact eomma.

00:10:20.182 --> 00:10:22.476
Here, it's the ekiben you've been
dreaming about.

00:10:22.560 --> 00:10:23.936
Really?

00:10:24.019 --> 00:10:25.730
-You bought it for me?
-Yeah.

00:10:26.564 --> 00:10:28.691
You said you saw it in an anime, right?

00:10:28.774 --> 00:10:31.193
Yeah, it's always been my dream.

00:10:32.403 --> 00:10:33.821
Thank you, Taiga.

00:10:44.123 --> 00:10:46.584
Wow! It's a real ekiben!

00:10:50.713 --> 00:10:51.547
Here.

00:10:58.721 --> 00:10:59.764
How is it?

00:11:00.514 --> 00:11:01.849
It's good.

00:11:04.351 --> 00:11:06.562
Ekiben is good even when it's cold.

00:11:07.938 --> 00:11:09.231
Taiga, eat with me.

00:11:09.857 --> 00:11:12.109
Okay, I'll try it too.

00:11:19.283 --> 00:11:21.076
-I'm full.
-Baebulleo.

00:11:27.583 --> 00:11:31.378
We were able to check one more thing
off your bucket list.

00:11:33.047 --> 00:11:34.256
That's right!

00:11:45.601 --> 00:11:48.854
Wait, you've done
more than half of them already.

00:11:50.356 --> 00:11:51.649
Thanks to you.

00:12:04.286 --> 00:12:05.246
‎Hey.

00:12:07.665 --> 00:12:08.749
It's too bad.

00:12:10.167 --> 00:12:13.045
Your proposal made it pretty far, though.

00:12:17.675 --> 00:12:18.551
Ms. Park?

00:12:20.302 --> 00:12:21.512
I'm sorry.

00:12:23.055 --> 00:12:24.598
Thank you.

00:12:26.684 --> 00:12:30.688
It was a nice experience for me
and I learned a lot.

00:12:35.734 --> 00:12:37.027
You know,

00:12:37.111 --> 00:12:41.198
it was so much fun and so exciting.

00:12:41.282 --> 00:12:44.660
I feel like this is the kind of job
that I want to do.

00:12:49.748 --> 00:12:51.917
I'm sure you will, Ms. Park.

00:12:53.127 --> 00:12:53.961
What?

00:12:54.044 --> 00:12:56.130
I can see a sparkle in your eyes.

00:12:59.508 --> 00:13:02.469
Whatever you are feeling right now,
don't forget it.

00:13:04.221 --> 00:13:05.139
Yes.

00:13:05.931 --> 00:13:07.558
Thank you.

00:13:08.809 --> 00:13:11.729
Thank you for everything
you've done for me.

00:13:11.812 --> 00:13:14.690
No, thank you.

00:13:15.524 --> 00:13:18.027
I'll do my best to find a job.

00:13:19.945 --> 00:13:22.072
Isn't it too late
to start job hunting now?

00:13:23.157 --> 00:13:25.075
You graduate in two months.

00:13:25.159 --> 00:13:27.536
Is anybody hiring new grads still?

00:13:28.120 --> 00:13:29.413
Yeah…

00:13:29.496 --> 00:13:32.625
The window for hiring new grads
is basically closed,

00:13:33.250 --> 00:13:38.464
so I will be mainly
looking for mid-career recruitments.

00:13:41.425 --> 00:13:43.510
What if none of the companies
want to hire you?

00:13:45.179 --> 00:13:48.015
Even if that happens,
I'll just do everything that I can.

00:13:48.932 --> 00:13:51.310
I won't lose focus anymore.

00:13:52.936 --> 00:13:56.106
For now, I'm making a list
of advertising companies in Japan

00:13:56.190 --> 00:13:59.526
and analyzing
their different business styles.

00:13:59.610 --> 00:14:01.070
You're serious, aren't you?

00:14:02.279 --> 00:14:04.198
You have a different look about you.

00:14:09.370 --> 00:14:10.496
All right then.

00:14:11.121 --> 00:14:14.291
After all, it's the first time you've
decided to do something on your own.

00:14:16.043 --> 00:14:20.089
Up until now, it seemed like you were
just doing things out of obligation.

00:14:22.049 --> 00:14:23.801
Yung-yeol…

00:14:25.010 --> 00:14:26.553
Do what you feel is right.

00:14:27.096 --> 00:14:28.514
I'll be rooting for you.

00:14:30.182 --> 00:14:31.141
Okay.

00:14:33.435 --> 00:14:37.356
MAMAMON

00:14:43.904 --> 00:14:45.823
Now is the time to do it.

00:14:58.085 --> 00:15:01.797
Oh, why are you calling at this hour?

00:15:01.880 --> 00:15:03.882
Have you eaten already?

00:15:04.591 --> 00:15:05.968
Yeah, I just ate.

00:15:07.803 --> 00:15:11.056
About the instructor position
you talked about…

00:15:12.016 --> 00:15:14.351
You finally made up your mind?

00:15:14.435 --> 00:15:15.811
You're taking it, right?

00:15:17.730 --> 00:15:18.856
I'm sorry,

00:15:19.398 --> 00:15:22.401
but I want you to turn it down.

00:15:23.652 --> 00:15:24.528
What?

00:15:25.195 --> 00:15:28.032
I want to work in advertising.

00:15:28.115 --> 00:15:30.034
So I'm going to look for a job in Japan.

00:15:33.120 --> 00:15:34.329
Wait a second.

00:15:34.413 --> 00:15:37.916
Looking for a job in Japan?

00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:40.669
And in advertising?

00:15:40.753 --> 00:15:43.756
What happened to animation?

00:15:43.839 --> 00:15:46.258
It may seem like I made a detour,

00:15:46.759 --> 00:15:50.804
but it's because I majored in animation
that I found an interest in advertising.

00:15:51.472 --> 00:15:52.473
Anyway,

00:15:53.307 --> 00:15:55.851
I'm going to do my best to find a job.

00:15:58.270 --> 00:15:59.396
Hello?

00:16:22.836 --> 00:16:25.297
Huh? Are you moving or what?

00:16:27.674 --> 00:16:29.218
Not right away.

00:16:29.885 --> 00:16:31.261
But soon.

00:16:31.345 --> 00:16:32.554
Really?

00:16:32.638 --> 00:16:34.640
Then this time,

00:16:34.723 --> 00:16:37.434
I'd like a place that's closer
to the station.

00:16:41.438 --> 00:16:44.525
It's not going to be around here.

00:16:45.567 --> 00:16:50.781
Oh, really? A new town? How exciting.

00:17:06.588 --> 00:17:08.382
It's open! Just come in!

00:17:12.219 --> 00:17:15.305
Tada! It's a good luck treat!

00:17:15.973 --> 00:17:18.225
Mochi? You made it, Rin?

00:17:18.892 --> 00:17:19.726
‎Yeah.

00:17:20.561 --> 00:17:22.312
It's called chapssal-tteok.

00:17:23.105 --> 00:17:26.942
Usually, you're supposed to gift it
to someone before their entrance exam.

00:17:27.025 --> 00:17:28.402
I'm sorry it's late.

00:17:28.485 --> 00:17:30.112
Don't be.

00:17:30.195 --> 00:17:32.739
Thank you for making it for me.

00:17:34.575 --> 00:17:36.702
It's because you looked so worried.

00:17:37.995 --> 00:17:40.998
You know how mochi
is really sticky, right?

00:17:41.081 --> 00:17:44.001
So you give it to them in hopes that

00:17:44.084 --> 00:17:47.254
success sticks to them like mochi.

00:17:47.337 --> 00:17:48.964
I see.

00:17:49.548 --> 00:17:51.383
Do you put red bean paste inside
or something?

00:17:51.466 --> 00:17:55.095
Yeah. Cocoa powder, red bean paste,

00:17:55.179 --> 00:17:58.390
and wal… walnuts go inside.

00:17:58.473 --> 00:18:01.101
I know it's going to be kkulmat already.

00:18:01.685 --> 00:18:03.061
There you go again with "kkulmat."

00:18:03.979 --> 00:18:05.439
Oh? Hold on…

00:18:07.399 --> 00:18:08.775
Stop playing around.

00:18:08.859 --> 00:18:11.278
-Sorry, sorry.
-Stop it.

00:18:14.823 --> 00:18:16.366
It might be documents from my work.

00:18:17.284 --> 00:18:19.077
I can accept the delivery.

00:18:19.161 --> 00:18:20.787
Will you do that? Thank you.

00:18:20.871 --> 00:18:22.039
Okay.

00:18:23.749 --> 00:18:25.459
Yes, yes, coming!

00:18:29.171 --> 00:18:31.173
Who are you?

00:18:33.342 --> 00:18:36.094
This is my daughter's room.

00:18:38.472 --> 00:18:39.473
Mom!

00:18:53.862 --> 00:18:56.823
Mom, this is my boyfriend.

00:19:00.619 --> 00:19:01.828
Annyeonghaseyo.

00:19:03.956 --> 00:19:05.123
Nice to meet you.

00:19:05.791 --> 00:19:06.792
Um…

00:19:07.459 --> 00:19:10.045
Jeoneun Hase Taiga imnida.

00:19:13.924 --> 00:19:15.259
"Boyfriend"?

00:19:16.343 --> 00:19:20.055
Here I thought you were
working hard on your graduation project,

00:19:20.138 --> 00:19:21.640
not bringing a man home!

00:19:21.723 --> 00:19:23.684
Don't say it like that.

00:19:23.767 --> 00:19:24.643
Park Rin,

00:19:24.726 --> 00:19:28.522
why do you think I let you study abroad?

00:19:28.605 --> 00:19:31.566
Why do you think I have been

00:19:31.650 --> 00:19:34.736
supporting you this whole time?

00:19:34.820 --> 00:19:38.073
I paid for your rent and living expenses
for what?

00:19:39.032 --> 00:19:42.202
It's so that you can focus on studying.
Isn't that right?

00:19:42.286 --> 00:19:44.913
It's not like I'm slacking off at school.

00:19:45.664 --> 00:19:49.459
Taiga and I are supporting each other,
and he helps me.

00:19:50.585 --> 00:19:52.713
Oh, is that right?

00:19:52.796 --> 00:19:55.924
Then why have you been hiding it from me?

00:19:56.008 --> 00:19:58.302
Because I knew you'd be like this!

00:20:00.053 --> 00:20:01.763
You don't have to overreact like that.

00:20:05.100 --> 00:20:08.145
Sorry, Taiga. Can you leave for today?

00:20:08.228 --> 00:20:09.354
What?

00:20:09.980 --> 00:20:11.732
I'll talk to her.

00:20:13.984 --> 00:20:15.319
Okay.

00:20:16.069 --> 00:20:17.446
I'll contact you later.

00:20:36.423 --> 00:20:38.050
You're going to find a job in Japan?

00:20:38.133 --> 00:20:40.385
What are you even thinking?

00:20:40.469 --> 00:20:42.637
Like I said, I want to try it out.

00:20:43.764 --> 00:20:45.557
And advertising at that?

00:20:45.640 --> 00:20:48.685
What was the point of studying
animation this whole time?

00:20:48.769 --> 00:20:52.647
You're only saying that
to be with your boyfriend, aren't you?

00:20:52.731 --> 00:20:58.070
Why would you make a decision
on a whim like that?

00:20:58.153 --> 00:21:00.989
It's not on a whim!

00:21:01.073 --> 00:21:03.325
I thought hard about it
and chose this path.

00:21:03.408 --> 00:21:05.077
How many times must I tell you?

00:21:05.160 --> 00:21:07.371
Life isn't that easy!

00:21:08.497 --> 00:21:10.749
Going into the advertising industry now?

00:21:10.832 --> 00:21:12.292
There's no way you'll succeed.

00:21:16.380 --> 00:21:17.422
Whatever.

00:21:17.923 --> 00:21:20.759
I don't have time to be
playing along with your whims.

00:21:20.842 --> 00:21:23.887
Once you graduate,
you will return to Korea right away.

00:21:29.017 --> 00:21:30.936
Mom, I've had enough.

00:21:31.978 --> 00:21:33.188
Excuse me?

00:21:34.231 --> 00:21:36.566
You've been suffocating me like that
this whole time.

00:21:36.650 --> 00:21:38.610
When you don't even know anything.

00:21:38.693 --> 00:21:43.031
I'm not a child anymore.
I can't stand you meddling in my life.

00:21:43.115 --> 00:21:45.409
It's my life, so just leave me alone!

00:22:21.194 --> 00:22:22.195
Hello?

00:22:22.279 --> 00:22:25.991
Taiga, what should I do?
Eomma still isn't back.

00:22:26.074 --> 00:22:27.033
What?

00:22:27.784 --> 00:22:30.036
It's because I said
horrible things to her.

00:22:48.763 --> 00:22:49.931
Ma'am!

00:22:51.183 --> 00:22:52.475
Oh, I'm sorry.

00:23:05.197 --> 00:23:06.948
Oh, excuse me!

00:23:07.532 --> 00:23:09.075
Have you seen this person?

00:23:10.410 --> 00:23:12.037
Okay, thank you.

00:23:43.610 --> 00:23:44.778
Ma'am!

00:23:45.612 --> 00:23:46.738
Um…

00:23:46.821 --> 00:23:47.697
Ma'am…

00:23:47.781 --> 00:23:49.074
um…

00:23:49.741 --> 00:23:52.244
Rin! Rin is waiting for you.

00:23:56.039 --> 00:23:57.791
What are you here for?

00:23:59.793 --> 00:24:00.794
Yes?

00:24:06.508 --> 00:24:08.385
It's just as they say.

00:24:08.468 --> 00:24:10.387
Children don't know
how their parents feel.

00:24:13.056 --> 00:24:16.476
She talks about finding a job
like it's so simple.

00:24:17.018 --> 00:24:20.355
But what if she can't find anything
and gets hurt,

00:24:20.438 --> 00:24:22.732
and regrets her choice later on?

00:24:31.616 --> 00:24:32.784
Ma'am…

00:24:36.079 --> 00:24:40.875
All I'm saying is that I don't want
to see her go through hardships.

00:24:42.252 --> 00:24:44.045
What's wrong with that?

00:24:45.171 --> 00:24:48.091
She may call it

00:24:48.717 --> 00:24:52.846
"meddling" and that's fine with me.

00:24:54.389 --> 00:24:55.974
If that's what it takes

00:24:56.933 --> 00:25:00.979
to keep her from getting hurt.

00:25:01.062 --> 00:25:02.814
That's all that matters.

00:25:10.822 --> 00:25:12.532
What you're saying…

00:25:15.952 --> 00:25:17.912
I don't understand it,

00:25:19.247 --> 00:25:20.498
but I get it.

00:25:22.542 --> 00:25:24.336
I get that you care about Rin.

00:25:25.879 --> 00:25:27.088
So…

00:25:28.089 --> 00:25:30.633
please tell Rin what you just said.

00:25:35.180 --> 00:25:37.057
What is he saying?

00:25:39.768 --> 00:25:42.395
But first…

00:25:46.149 --> 00:25:48.276
Have you eaten?

00:27:43.516 --> 00:27:44.934
Thank you for waiting.

00:27:46.060 --> 00:27:48.396
‎TANOMI

00:27:49.230 --> 00:27:52.984
This is the Park family's gimbap
that Rin taught me how to make.

00:27:54.360 --> 00:27:56.362
I wanted to serve it to you.

00:28:02.660 --> 00:28:03.495
Enjoy.

00:28:28.269 --> 00:28:30.104
This is…

00:28:34.317 --> 00:28:35.527
Eomma!

00:28:45.745 --> 00:28:46.746
Sorry…

00:28:47.413 --> 00:28:49.541
Can you please translate

00:28:49.624 --> 00:28:51.835
what I'm going to say to your mother?

00:28:52.585 --> 00:28:53.795
Huh?

00:28:54.462 --> 00:28:56.714
Okay, sure.

00:29:08.935 --> 00:29:11.271
I heard from Rin that on the days

00:29:11.855 --> 00:29:14.649
you make gimbap,
the whole house smells good,

00:29:14.732 --> 00:29:18.194
and it makes her feel very happy.

00:29:40.258 --> 00:29:44.345
Rin loves her family more than anything.

00:29:46.472 --> 00:29:48.641
When you send her side dishes,

00:29:48.725 --> 00:29:52.395
she eats them little by little
and savors each one.

00:29:52.979 --> 00:29:55.607
When she sees news
about something happening in Korea,

00:29:56.149 --> 00:29:59.819
she immediately writes on her family chat.

00:30:20.798 --> 00:30:22.467
To be honest,

00:30:22.967 --> 00:30:26.638
I don't have that close of a relationship
with my family.

00:30:27.513 --> 00:30:31.392
And so I was a little envious of Rin.

00:30:33.227 --> 00:30:35.063
But I think it's beautiful.

00:30:54.040 --> 00:30:56.668
In my opinion, Rin is able to do her best

00:30:57.543 --> 00:30:59.462
in a foreign land like this

00:30:59.545 --> 00:31:02.465
because she has somewhere
she can return to at any time.

00:31:19.691 --> 00:31:21.025
So…

00:31:26.239 --> 00:31:27.699
Please…

00:31:30.451 --> 00:31:34.706
Will you put just a little bit of trust
in the path that Rin chose,

00:31:35.581 --> 00:31:37.375
and watch over her?

00:31:45.049 --> 00:31:48.136
So, Mom, please…

00:31:53.433 --> 00:31:58.312
Will you trust the path that I chose
and watch over me?

00:32:19.000 --> 00:32:20.043
Eomma?

00:32:24.672 --> 00:32:26.174
Just the thought of you

00:32:27.467 --> 00:32:32.305
telling me,
"I don't need your help anymore"

00:32:33.806 --> 00:32:38.061
scared me more than anything.

00:32:41.564 --> 00:32:42.607
I wished

00:32:43.399 --> 00:32:47.987
that you would always look to me for help.

00:32:48.905 --> 00:32:51.115
I knew in my head

00:32:51.699 --> 00:32:53.826
that it wasn't possible.

00:32:53.910 --> 00:32:58.039
But to me,

00:32:59.499 --> 00:33:03.503
that is what brings the most happiness.

00:33:11.969 --> 00:33:13.304
Eomma…

00:33:38.371 --> 00:33:41.541
Make sure you rest well tonight.
Take care.

00:33:42.625 --> 00:33:44.836
Thank you for today, Taiga.

00:33:47.755 --> 00:33:48.631
How do you say "it was delicious"?

00:33:54.262 --> 00:33:55.513
Jeogi…

00:33:56.806 --> 00:33:57.974
It was delicious.

00:34:06.190 --> 00:34:07.441
Gamsahamnida.

00:34:19.203 --> 00:34:20.746
Mom, are you asleep?

00:34:31.299 --> 00:34:33.467
I'm sorry I said
horrible things to you today.

00:34:36.804 --> 00:34:38.973
I worked as an intern,

00:34:39.056 --> 00:34:41.726
and felt like that's where I belonged.

00:34:42.810 --> 00:34:45.188
It's my first time feeling that way.

00:34:48.900 --> 00:34:51.736
I've made you worry a lot up until now,

00:34:52.528 --> 00:34:55.156
so I'll do everything I can to find a job.

00:34:57.158 --> 00:34:58.034
Okay?

00:35:04.165 --> 00:35:06.834
I don't really understand,

00:35:09.295 --> 00:35:11.464
but go ahead and do your best.

00:35:13.549 --> 00:35:17.220
If you can't take it anymore,
don't hesitate to tell me.

00:35:19.764 --> 00:35:21.807
Thank you, Mom.

00:35:35.863 --> 00:35:40.534
TAIGA: DID YOUR MOTHER GET HOME SAFELY?

00:35:40.618 --> 00:35:42.787
YEAH. I TOOK HER TO THE AIRPORT.

00:35:42.870 --> 00:35:47.041
HOSHIUMI ASAKO - INTERNSHIP

00:35:48.960 --> 00:35:50.044
Hello?

00:35:52.421 --> 00:35:53.297
Oh, yes.

00:36:00.596 --> 00:36:05.142
MY PAGE LOGIN

00:36:05.226 --> 00:36:06.394
ACCEPTED

00:36:09.647 --> 00:36:10.815
Yes!

00:36:17.947 --> 00:36:20.908
Rin! I got accepted!

00:36:20.992 --> 00:36:22.994
What? Really?

00:36:23.869 --> 00:36:25.663
Congratulations, Taiga.

00:36:25.746 --> 00:36:26.914
Thanks.

00:36:26.998 --> 00:36:29.959
I'm so glad!

00:36:32.962 --> 00:36:34.255
Actually,

00:36:35.298 --> 00:36:38.301
I just got a call from work too.

00:36:40.011 --> 00:36:41.012
Huh?

00:36:42.346 --> 00:36:44.015
I got an offer…

00:36:46.517 --> 00:36:48.769
from the Korean advertising company

00:36:49.520 --> 00:36:50.980
from the contest the other day.

00:36:52.440 --> 00:36:55.609
That's amazing! Congratulations.

00:36:59.697 --> 00:37:00.698
Wait…

00:37:02.325 --> 00:37:05.036
Did you say "Korean"?

00:37:09.248 --> 00:37:10.416
Yeah.

00:37:17.757 --> 00:37:19.300
Does that mean…

00:37:22.845 --> 00:37:24.347
you're going back?

00:37:30.019 --> 00:37:33.230
Maybe.

00:37:39.945 --> 00:37:41.155
I see.

00:37:50.539 --> 00:37:53.876
I'll be fine.

00:37:55.503 --> 00:37:59.423
If this will let you follow
the path you chose, I'm happy.

00:38:03.427 --> 00:38:04.678
I told you, remember?

00:38:05.429 --> 00:38:07.431
No matter where you go,

00:38:07.515 --> 00:38:09.475
I'll make sure I can support you.

00:38:11.560 --> 00:38:13.938
But nothing is set yet.

00:38:14.855 --> 00:38:16.649
First, I'll do my best at the interview.

00:38:19.944 --> 00:38:20.945
You can do it.

00:38:33.040 --> 00:38:34.083
PREVIEW

00:38:34.166 --> 00:38:35.292
But I…

00:38:37.169 --> 00:38:38.003
I…

00:38:40.464 --> 00:38:41.841
I was saved by you.

00:38:41.924 --> 00:38:42.967
THIS DRAMA IS FICTION AND ALL CHARACTERS
AND ORGANIZATIONS ARE FICTIONAL

00:38:43.050 --> 00:38:43.926
Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita